<h3>Difference b/w renaissance man and woman&nbsp;</h3>
<p>woman = not seek fame, be educated about art + be pleasing , inspire art but rarely create it.</p>
<p>man = Create art and accomplished in various fields of study.</p>
<h3>Renaissance in literature and art&nbsp;</h3>
<p>Petrarch - earliest humanist + committed to christianity = cultivate literary eloquents inspire people to do good. (ETHICAL WISDOM)</p>
<p>--&gt;&nbsp; Classical latin for ethical wisdom -- first step to renaissance&nbsp;</p>
